Serves: 4-6Ingredients:6 quality pork or beef sausagesOlive oil125ml ( cup) sparkling or dry white wine500g seedless white grapes on the stalk, washed and cut into small bunchesKnob of butterGrinding of black pepperHandful of flat leaf parsley, choppedChicken with red wine & grapes Method:1) Prick sausages with a fork and cook in a frying pan with dash of olive oil till golden brown all over.2) Add the wine and grapes and cook till grapes release their juices and are heated through.3) Add a knob of butter, season with black pepper, and serve sprinkled with parsley.